n%20rate%20in%20money%20laundering%20cases%20and%20asked%20how%20long%20the%20senior%20politician%20can%20be%20kept%20behind%20bars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Chatterjee%2C%20once%20a%20trusted%20lieutenant%20of%20Trinamool%20chief%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20the%20Education%20Minister%20in%20her%20cabinet%2C%20was%20arrested%20in%20July%202022%20in%20a%20money%20laundering%20case%20linked%20to%20the%20alleged%20teacher%20recruitment%20scam%20in%20the%20state.%20He%20has%20since%20been%20removed%20as%20minister%20and%20suspended%20from%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20Advocate%20Mukul%20Rohatgi%2C%20appearing%20for%20Mr%20Chatterjee%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20trial%20is%20yet%20to%20begin%20and%20the%20veteran%20leader%20has%20already%20been%20in%20jail%20for%202.5%20years%20in%20a%20case%20in%20which%20the%20punishment%20is%207-year%20imprisonment.%20%26quot%3BTrial%20is%20yet%20to%20start%2C%20there%20are%20183%20witnesses%2C%20four%20supplementary%20prosecution%20complaints%2C%20he%20is%2073%20years%20of%20age%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Mr%20Rohatgi%20said%20that%20even%20Mr%20Chatterjee's%20aide%20Arpita%20Mukherjee%2C%20from%20whose%20home%20a%20mountain%20of%20cash%20was%20recovered%2C%20has%20been%20granted%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditional%20Solicitor%20General%20SV%20Raju%20said%20it%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bbig%20case%20in%20which%20people%20were%20deprived%20of%20jobs%20and%20undeserving%20candidates%20appointed%26quot%3B.%20He%20said%20Arpita%20Mukherjee%20had%20said%20that%20the%20massive%20cash%20recovered%20from%20her%20premises%20belonged%20to%20Partha%20Chatterjee.%20Mr%20Rohatgi%20said%20nothing%20was%20recovered%20from%20the%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Surya%20Kant%20and%20Justice%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20trial%20was%20yet%20to%20begin%20and%20hundreds%20of%20witnesses%20needed%20to%20be%20examined.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20the%20only%20case%20pending%20before%20the%20court%20you%20see...%20how%20long%20can%20we%20keep%20him%20behind%20bars%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20acknowledging%20that%20the%20ED%20has%20a%20Herculean%20task%20on%20its%20hands%20and%20the%20allegations%20against%20the%20minister%20are%20%26quot%3Bvery%20serious%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20in%20the%20ultimate%20analysis%2C%20he%20is%20not%20convicted%2C%20then%20what%20will%20happen%3F%20what%20will%20happen%20to%20the%20three%20years%20gone%20by.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20then%20asked%20the%20Centre's%20lawyer%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20your%20conviction%20rate%20for%20ED%3F%20It%20is%20very%2C%20very%20poor...%20We%20would%20have%20understood%20if%20it%20was%2060%20to%2070%20percent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Raju%20said%20he%20was%20sure%20the%20minister%20would%20be%20convicted%20in%20this%20case%20and%20sentenced%20to%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20bench%20asked%20what%20will%20happen%20if%20he%20was%20released%20on%20bail%2C%20the%20Centre's%20lawyer%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20a%20retraction%20of%20statements%20by%20witnesses.%20Arpita%20is%20a%20close%20aide%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Mr%20Rohatgi%20said%20it%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bhorrendous%20argument%26quot%3B%2C%20Mr%20Raju%20replied%20it%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bhorrendous%20crime%26quot%3B.%20The%20Centre's%20lawyer%20said%20this%20was%20not%20a%20case%20to%20exercise%20discretion.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20about%20neck-deep%20corruption...%20there%20are%20extreme%20and%20soft%20cases%2C%20this%20is%20an%20extreme%20case.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Rohatgi%20said%20the%20delay%20in%20the%20start%20of%20trial%20is%20the%20government's%20problem.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20the%20law%20of%20bail%20and%20this%20court%20has%20tried%20to%20correct%20and%20steady%20the%20law%20on%20bail%20in%20the%20last%20six%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%2