even%20if%20we%20got%20serious%3A%20Work%20had%20to%20be%20enjoyable%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%26quot%3B%20Chouinard%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BWe%20needed%20to%20blur%20that%20distinction%20between%20work%20and%20play%20and%20family.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20founding%20in%201973%2C%20Patagonia%20has%20positioned%20itself%20as%20a%20workplace%20nirvana%20%E2%80%94%20a%20community%20more%20so%20than%20a%20company%2C%20one%20that%20prioritizes%20the%20well-being%20of%20the%20Earth%20and%20of%20its%20employees%20above%20all%20else.%20But%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20as%20sales%20have%20slowed%2C%20the%20outdoor-apparel%20brand%20has%20buckled%20down%2C%20cutting%20redundant%20jobs%2C%20tracking%20performance%20metrics%2C%20and%20banning%20long-standing%20practices%20such%20as%20letting%20sales%20representatives%20sell%20Patagonia%20samples%20to%20friends%20and%20family%20on%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20also%20started%20to%20respond%20to%20customers'%20demand%20for%20delivery%20at%20Amazon%20speed.%20The%20rejiggering%20is%20a%20means%20of%20survival%2C%20a%20necessity%2C%20Patagonia%20says%2C%20to%20provide%20for%20its%203%2C000-plus%20employees.%20But%20the%20retailer%20is%20now%20dealing%20with%20the%20fallout%20from%20disappointed%20staffers%20who%20say%20the%20new%20rigidity%20feels%20antithetical%20to%20the%20company's%20ethos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20always%20been%20a%20self-critical%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20Vincent%20Stanley%2C%20Patagonia's%20director%20of%20philosophy%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhenever%20the%20company%20does%20something%20that's%20not%20well%20understood%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20values%2C%20you%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20internal%20reaction%20to%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPatagonia%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpatagonia-yvon-chouinard-environment-staff-benefits-sustainability-childcare-organic-donate-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20billion-dollar%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20more%20than%2070%20stores%20worldwide.%20The%20brand's%20%24130%20vests%20and%20%24280%20jackets%20are%20just%20as%20likely%20to%20be%20sported%20on%20Wall%20Street%20as%20in%20the%20great%20outdoors%20%E2%80%94%20earning%20it%20the%20nickname%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpatagonia-mocks-wall-street-twitter-fleece-vest-drama-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPatagucci%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Patagonia's%20commitment%20to%20do%20good%20is%20integral%20to%20the%20brand.%20Over%20the%20years%20it%20has%20donated%20the%20equivalent%20of%20%24226%20million%20to%20environmental%20causes%2C%20and%20in%202001%20it%20created%20an%20Earth%20tax%2C%20pledging%201%25%20of%20sales%20to%20preserve%20and%20restore%20the%20natural%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatagonia's%20sales%20soared%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20From%20summer%202020%20to%20summer%202022%2C%20sales%20grew%20at%20a%20rate%20of%20about%2020%25%20to%2025%25%20companywide%2C%20Alan%20Adams%2C%20a%20former%20US%20regional%20sales%20rep%20for%20Montana%2C%20Wyoming%2C%20and%20Alaska%2C%20told%20BI.%20Adams%2C%20who%20left%20the%20company%20in%202023%2C%20said%20COVID-19%20restrictions%20led%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Bunsustainable%26quot%3B%20boom%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20renewed%20interest%20in%20outdoor%20activities%20had%20people%20stocking%20up%20on%20all-weather%20gear%20and%20apparel.%20For%20a%20period%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcovid-surges-largest-us-port-threaten-more-delays-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20California%20ports%20faced%20major%20backlogs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Patagonia%20relied%20on%20planes%20to%20transport%20about%20a%20third%20of%20its%20goods.%20(Before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20about%2080%25%20of%20Patagonia%20stock%20was%20shipped%20by%20barge%2C%20a%20decidedly%20more%20environmentally%20friendly%20option.)%20A%20Patagonia%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20it%20uses%20less%20air%20freight%20now%20than%20it%20did%20before%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224427%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22April%209%2C%202020%20file%20photo%20shows%20a%20closed%20Patagonia%20clothing%20store%20in%20Freeport%2C%20Maine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c72350c72ebc54a40dd9ac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222951%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Patagonia%20clothing%20store%20in%20Freeport%2C%20Maine%2C%20in%20April%202020.%3Cp%3ERobert%20F.%20Bukaty%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPatagonia%20started%20to%20attract%20a%20new%20customer%20base%20less%20attached%20to%20its%20green%20credentials%20and%20more%20demanding%20of%20superspeed%20delivery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20do%20to%20make%20the%20customer%20happy%20and%20to%20save%20ourselves%20from%20backlash%20is%20not%20environmentally%20sustainable%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20current%20customer-service%2C%20or%20CX%2C%20manager%20who%20has%20been%20at%20the%20company%20for%20multiple%20years.%20%26quot%3BIf%20someone%20doesn't%20like%20their%20repair%2C%20it%20doesn't%20match%20perfectly%2C%20then%20we%20ship%20them%20a%20new%20item%20overnight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Patagonia%20spokesperson%20said%20it%20had%20been%20tricky%20to%20navigate%20the%20demand%20for%20instant%20gratification.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20don't%20know%20is%20how%20do%20we%20support%20our%20customer-service%20team%20when%20customers%20are%20like%2C%20'Well%2C%20Amazon%20sends%20it%20to%20me%20overnight.%20Why%20can't%20Patagonia%3F'%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20She%20added%20that%20Patagonia%20has%20an%20%26quot%3Bironclad%20guarantee%26quot%3B%20to%20give%20customers%20a%20new%20item%20if%20they%20don't%20like%20a%20repair.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhile%20overnight%20shipping%20is%20an%20option%2C%20Patagonia%20tries%20to%20direct%20customers%20away%20from%20that%20choice%20with%20pricing%20and%20messaging%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20said%20Chouinard%2C%20now%2086%2C%20was%20typically%20one%20to%20challenge%20decisions%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpatagonia-mission-environmentalism-good-for-business-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprioritized%20profit%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20sustainability.%20Adams%20recalled%20that%20at%20an%20event%20in%20about%202013%20in%20Idaho%2C%20Chouinard%20seemed%20shocked%20at%20how%20large%20Patagonia's%20sales%20representatives'%20trucks%20were.%20He%20kicked%20a%20tire%20and%20asked%20one%20rep%3A%20%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20you%20have%20this%20huge%20truck%3F%20That's%20not%20what%20we're%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202022%2C%20Chouinard%2C%20who%20sits%20on%20Patagonia's%20board%2C%20announced%20that%20he%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpatagonia-founder-gives-away-company-profits-to-go-climate-crisis-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egiving%20away%20his%20shares%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20company%20to%20a%20newly%20formed%20trust%20to%20fight%20the%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221154%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yvon%20Chouinard%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F636537b100d7c600187837c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221154%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYvon%20Chouinard%2C%20Patagonia's%20founder%2C%20gave%20away%20his%20shares%20in%20the%20company%20in%20September%202022.%3Cp%3ECampbell%20Brewer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20about%20this%20time%2C%20Patagonia%20began%20reassessing%20its%20operations.%20For%20the%20better%20part%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20the%20senior%20leadership%20team%20was%20%26quot%3Blocked%20in%20a%20room%26quot%3B%20figuring%20out%20which%20priorities%20they%20weren't%20achieving%20and%20how%20decision-making%20could%20be%20improved.%20They%20also%20hired%20consultants%20to%20help%20restructure%20the%20company%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20employees%20felt%20as%20though%20Patagonia's%20new%20direction%20directly%20threatened%20the%20utopia%20they%20%E2%80%94%20and%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20had%20been%20sold.%20A%20worker%20from%20the%20digital%20team%20expressed%20concern%20about%20Patagonia's%20buy-now%2C%20pay-later%20feature%20that%20launched%20this%20past%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20it's%20encouraging%20people%20to%20spend%20more%20money%20than%20they%20can%20currently%20afford%2C%20and%20buy%20more%20things%20that%20they%20don't%20need%2C%20which%20goes%20directly%20against%20Patagonia's%20mission%20and%20anti-consumption%20message%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStanley%2C%20the%20company's%20director%20of%20philosophy%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20growth%20had%20brought%20about%20%26quot%3Bcomplicated%20decisions%26quot%3B%20like%20how%20to%20balance%20the%20long-term%20business%20health%20against%20the%20company's%20core%20values%20while%20providing%20a%20consistent%20level%20of%20benefits%20to%20all%20employees.%20Financial%20stability%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20crucial%20for%20Patagonia%20to%20honor%20its%20commitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20companies%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Patagonia%20was%20left%20with%20a%20surplus%20of%20staff%20and%20inventory%2C%20Adams%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20it%20has%20tried%20to%20rein%20in%20costs%20and%20streamline%20business%20operations.%20In%20the%20fall%20of%202022%2C%20Patagonia%20said%20it%20would%20stop%20allowing%20sales%20reps%20to%20sell%20extra%20clothing%20samples%20to%20their%20friends%20and%20family.%20Adams%2C%20who%20made%20about%20%24350%2C000%20in%202022%2C%20according%20to%20tax%20documents%20seen%20by%20BI%2C%20said%20this%20was%20a%20significant%20change.%20He%20said%20that%20even%20with%20a%20promised%20increase%20to%20his%20base%20salary%20and%20bonus%2C%20he%20would%20have%20expected%20to%20bring%20in%20just%20under%20%24200%2C000%20in%202023%20under%20the%20new%20rules.%20(The%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20salary%20increases%20and%20bonuses%20were%20meant%20to%20fully%20make%20up%20any%20differences%20in%20sales%20reps'%20total%20pay.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20year%2C%20Patagonia%20reversed%20a%20three-year-old%20policy%20of%20closing%20for%20the%20last%20week%20of%20December.%20The%20Patagonia%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20new%20policy%20asked%20CX%20and%20warehouse%20employees%20to%20volunteer%20for%20holiday%20shifts%20in%20order%20to%20ensure%20customers%20received%20service%20during%20the%20busy%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202023%2C%20Patagonia%20introduced%20a%20career-leveling%20plan%20for%20all%20US%20employees%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20more%20clearly%20define%20roles%20and%20match%20pay%20grades%20to%20the%20market%20standard.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20company%20also%20became%20more%20focused%20on%20tracking%20metrics%20across%20teams.%20%26quot%3BIt%20used%20to%20be%20that%20we%20would%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20a%20customer%20for%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20and%20just%20connect%20with%20them%20and%20talk%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CX%20employee%20who%20has%20been%20at%20Patagonia%20for%20multiple%20years%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20now%20we%20get%20dinged%20for%20having%20long%20phone%20calls.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Corey%20Simpson%20fields%20incoming%20calls%20at%20the%20reception%20desk%20at%20the%20Patagonia%20corporate%20headquarters%20in%20Ventura%2C%20California%20on%20Friday%2C%20September%2019%2C%202014%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d5b971289b805d1db36787%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20reception%20desk%20at%20Patagonia's%20headquarters%20in%20Ventura%2C%20California%2C%20in%202014.%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20though%2C%20the%20company%20began%20cutting%20jobs.%20In%20June%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpatagonia-cx-staff-told-to-relocate-or-leave-california-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPatagonia%20gave%2090%20employees%20on%20the%20CX%20team%2072%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20decide%20whether%20they%20wanted%20to%20relocate%20to%20one%20of%20seven%20US%20hubs%20or%20leave%20their%20jobs.%20Only%20four%20chose%20to%20relocate%2C%20according%20to%20an%20internal%20memo%20seen%20by%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Patagonia%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20changes%20were%20%26quot%3Bcrucial%20for%20us%20to%20build%20a%20vibrant%20team%20culture%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20CX%20team%20had%20been%20overstaffed%20by%20200%25%20to%20300%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20months%20later%2C%20Patagonia%20announced%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpatagonia-lays-off-41-workers-retail-sales-business-transformation-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E41%20corporate%20staffers%20had%20been%20let%20go%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20an%20internal%20memo%20sent%20the%20day%20the%20layoffs%20were%20announced%2C%20Stanley%20wrote%20that%20the%20company%20was%20experiencing%20the%20first%20sales%20decline%20in%20its%20history.%20In%20a%20follow-up%20FAQ%20about%20the%20layoffs%2C%20Stanley%20added%20that%20because%20of%20the%20financial%20strains%2C%20travel%20would%20be%20limited%2C%20bonuses%20would%20be%20lowered%2C%20and%20hiring%20would%20be%20paused%20across%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20told%20for%20years%20how%20important%20employees'%20happiness%20was%20and%20even%20being%20handed%20a%20book%20expounding%20these%20merits%2C%20workers%20were%20shaken.%20In%20%26quot%3BLet%20My%20People%20Go%20Surfing%2C%26quot%3B%20Chouinard%20called%20layoffs%20%26quot%3Balmost%20unthinkable%26quot%3B%20for%20Patagonia%20and%20described%20a%20round%20of%20job%20cuts%20in%201991%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20single%20darkest%20day%20in%20the%20company's%20history.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20people%20said%20the%2072-hour%20deadline%20for%20CX%20employees%20was%20insufficient%20to%20make%20such%20a%20major%20life%20decision.%20Another%20CX%20worker%20still%20at%20the%20company%20said%20the%20ultimatum%20was%20presented%20without%20%26quot%3Bdignity%20or%20care%20or%20anything%20that%20Patagonia%20stands%20for.%26quot%3B%20During%20a%20time%20when%20workers%20more%20generally%20were%20growing%20distrustful%20of%20their%20workplaces%2C%20many%20felt%20Patagonia%20was%20trying%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilent-lay-offs-quiet-firing-could-backfire-companies-bosses-morale-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20fire%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20staffers%2C%20with%20one%20employee%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Ban%20easy%20way%20for%20them%20to%20reduce%20their%20head%20count%20rather%20than%20waiting%20for%20attrition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yvon%20Chouinard%20and%20Vincent%20Stanley%20stand%20outside%20a%20yellow%20Patagonia%20store.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670e3fcfa70318649281c895%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChouinard%20with%20Vincent%20Stanley%2C%20the%20company's%20director%20of%20philosophy.%3Cp%3EPatagonia%20Works%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENick%20Helmreich%2C%20a%20team%20lead%20at%20Patagonia's%20store%20in%20Reno%2C%20Nevada%2C%20since%202022%2C%20recalled%20one%20colleague%20telling%20him%2C%20%26quot%3BCamelot%20is%20truly%20dead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20employees%20BI%20talked%20to%20said%20that%2C%20despite%20the%20recent%20upheavals%2C%20the%20company%20still%20t