20Moise's%20story%20is%20an%20example%20of%20the%20need%20to%20%26quot%3Bget%20it%20right%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoray%20advises%20that%20individuals%20start%20by%20reading%20the%20room%20and%20deciding%20whether%20their%20workplace%20is%20more%20conservative%20or%20relaxed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20they%20should%20take%20some%20time%20to%20consider%20who%20will%20read%20the%20email%20and%20why%20they%20want%20to%20add%20a%20casual%20tone%20or%20anecdote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAre%20you%20adding%20a%20wellness%20tip%20because%20you're%20the%20wellness%20committee%20chairperson%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAre%20you%20adding%20a%20historical%20factoid%20because%20you%20think%20they%20would%20be%20interested%2C%20or%20are%20you%20adding%20this%20so%20that%20you%20appear%20interesting%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoise%20told%20BI%20that%20she%20had%20found%20the%20response%20to%20her%20video%20funny%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20though%20some%20had%20veered%20into%20bullying%20or%20calling%20for%20her%20to%20be%20fired%2C%20which%20was%20%26quot%3Bunnecessary%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20people%20expressing%20negative%20thoughts%20are%20projecting%20their%20insecurities%20about%20being%20different%20or%20odd%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20incredibly%20accomplished%20on%20my%20own%20and%20have%20always%20navigated%20the%20workforce%20with%20ease.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoise's%20workplace%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fout-of-office-emails-ignited-debate-over-workplace-etiquette-tiktok-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732700449000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6744620dede4eeae3929434c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fw